ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: ID for the Experiment/settings/run
Number of current block within task
ID of current block
Number of trial within current block
Is the current trial an observe or a play trial?
Notes: 1 = Observe; 2 = Play

ElementDescription: What is the current goal token?
Notes: 1 = Green; 2 = Red; 3 = Blue

ElementDescription: Is the current trial a low-uncertainty (less similar token probabilities) or high-uncertainty (more similar token probabilities)?
Notes: 1 = Low Uncertainty; 2 = High Uncertainty

ElementDescription: Which action is unavailable (grayed out)?
Notes: 1 = Left; 2 = Middle; 3 = Right

ElementDescription: Which action is better (higher probability of winning goal token out of available actions)?
Which action is correct (highest probability of winning goal token)?
What order are colors stacked in slot machine image?
Notes: 1=GRB; 2=RBG; 3=BGR

ElementDescription: What is the order in which slot machines with different token probabilities appear; Green machine probability = G>R>B, red machine probabilty = R>B>G, blue machine probability = B>G>R
Notes: 1=G machine, R machine, B machine; 2=R machine, B machine, G machine; 3=B machine, G machine, R machine

ElementDescription: Indicates whether current trial will be followed by a break
Notes: 0=False; 1=True

ElementDescription: Which of the five videos available portraying the selected action is shown?
Notes: Defined for Observe trials, -999 for Play trials

ElementDescription: Observational Learning Task - Subject's response
Notes: Defined for Play trials, -999 for Observe trials. -999 in a Play trial indicates missed response (subject took longer than 4s)

ElementDescription: Time elapsed between stimulus onset and subject reponse
Notes: In seconds. Defined for Play trials, -999 for Observe trials. -999 in a Play trial indicates missed response (subject took longer than 4s)

ElementDescription: Did the subject select the better action during a play trial?
Notes: 0=False; 1=True. Defined for Play trials, -999 for Observe trials. -999 in a Play trial indicates missed response (subject took longer than 4s)

ElementDescription: Specifies token dispensed during a Play trial if subject responds Left
Notes: 1=Green; 2=Red; 3=Blue. Defined for Play trials, -999 for Observe trials.

ElementDescription: Specifies token dispensed during a Play trial if subject responds Middle
Notes: 1=Green; 2=Red; 3=Blue. Defined for Play trials, -999 for Observe trials.

ElementDescription: Specifies token dispensed during a Play trial if subject responds Right
Notes: 1=Green; 2=Red; 3=Blue. Defined for Play trials, -999 for Observe trials.

ElementDescription: Specifies token earned in a Play trial
Notes: 1=Green; 2=Red; 3=Blue. Defined for Play trials, -999 for Observe trials.

ElementDescription: Was the token earned in a play trial, the goal token?
Notes: 0=False; 1=True. Defined for Play trials;-999 for Observe trials. -999 in a Play trial indicates missed response (subject took longer than 4s)

ElementDescription: Value of token earned in a Play trial
Notes: 0 = Valued coin not dispensed; 10 = Valued coin was dispensed. Defined for Play trials; -999 for Observe trials. -999 in a Play trial indicates missed response (subject took longer than 4s)

ElementDescription: Did the subject take too long to respond to a Play trial?
Notes: 0=False; 1=True. Defined for Play trials; -999 for Observe trials.

ElementDescription: Is the trial a practice trial?
Notes: 0 = main task; 1 = practice

ElementDescription: Indicates whether subject made the correct response in trust quiz trial
Notes: 0 = False, 1 = True. Defined in trust quiz trials

ElementDescription: Rating of partner's trustworthiness before observational learning task
Notes: 0 = Lowest Rating; 5 = Highest Rating

ElementDescription: Rating of partner's trustworthiness after observational learning task
Notes: 0 = Lowest Rating; 5 = Highest Rating

ElementDescription: Rating of partner's predictability before observational learning task
Notes: 0 = Lowest Rating; 5 = Highest Rating

ElementDescription: Rating of partner's predictability after observational learning task
Notes: 0 = Lowest Rating; 5 = Highest Rating

ElementDescription: Rating of partner's competency before observational learning task
Notes: 0 = Lowest Rating; 5 = Highest Rating

ElementDescription: Rating of partner's competency after observational learning task
Notes: 0 = Lowest Rating; 5 = Highest Rating

ElementDescription: spouse partner conflict
Notes: 0=No; 1=Yes; -7=Refused

ElementDescription: Partner's trustworthiness level
Notes: Defined in trust game observation post-trial attention check, partner attribute rating, one-shot trust game, Play trials. 1 = Not Trustworthy; 2 = Neutral; 3 = Most Trustworthy

ElementDescription: One-shot trust game played with each partner with points from 0 to 10
Notes: Defined in one-shot trust game.

ElementDescription: Path to image shown in trust game post-trial attention check
Notes: Defined in trust game observation post-trial attention check

ElementDescription: Key pressed in trust game post-trial attention check asking how many points were exchanged
Notes: JavaScript keycode. Defined in trust game observation post-trial attention check

ElementDescription: Indicates whether subject pressed the correct key in trust game post-trial attention check
Notes: 0 = False, 1 = True. Defined in trust game observation post-trial attention check

ElementDescription: Trial number in trust quiz
Notes: Defined in trust quiz trials
